Description: Tools for constructing, evaluating, and optimizing experimental
    field designs for plant breeding and related agricultural applications.
    Provides two design families: (1) repeated-check block designs supporting
    augmented, partially replicated (p-rep), and RCBD-type layouts via
    prep_famoptg(), with evaluation by evaluate_famoptg_efficiency() and
    Random Restart optimisation by optimize_famoptg(); (2) fixed-grid alpha
    row-column stream designs with repeated checks via alpha_rc_stream(),
    with evaluation by evaluate_alpha_efficiency() and criterion-driven
    optimisation by optimize_alpha_rc() using Random Restart, Simulated
    Annealing, or a Genetic Algorithm. Both families support optional
    grouping from family labels or genomic and pedigree relationship matrices,
    optional post-layout genetic dispersion optimisation, and mixed-model
    efficiency evaluation under fixed or random treatment effects with IID,
    AR1, or AR1xAR1 residual structures. Efficiency criteria include
    A-optimality, D-optimality, and CDmean for genomic selection training
    population optimisation (Rincent et al. 2012
    <doi:10.1534/genetics.112.141473>). Large designs use a Hutchinson
    stochastic trace estimator (Hutchinson 1990
    <doi:10.1080/03610919008812866>) for scalable criterion approximation.
